					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-996202#post-3682905</guid>
				<title>It has no focus</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-996202/scp-2097#post-3682905</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 15 Jan 2018 21:35:06 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>EndlessNameless</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3617744</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I will agree with &quot;A Random Day&quot; post above, there is not enough focus on the anomaly of SCP-2097, and SCP-2097-02 didn't have enough personality (besides describing itself as related to a Mongolian deity) to hold my interest.<br /> The texts described in the Containment Procedures are not well explained (is it to fake Juan's presence? Also, he could comment something on the Mongolian ones, since the entity apparently participated in their History). Also, to be true in character in my opinion, SCP-2097-02 should not only speak in poor English, but in poor English <em>from the 1500s</em> as taught by a Spanish.<br /> It is just too random for my taste, sorry!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
